disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Headshot.

blurb.value: Innate: Every few basic attack Caitlyn will fire a headshot dealing bonus physical damage that scales with her  critical strike chance. On trapped or netted targets, Caitlyn's headshot  attack range is doubled.

description.value: Innate: Caitlyn's basic attacks generate a stack of Headshot on-attack, doubled when attacking from brush. At 6 stacks, or 5 while in brush, Caitlyn's next basic attack becomes unstoppable and deals (50 / 75 / 100% (based on level) + (125% +  15.625%) critical strike chance) AD bonus physical damage, increased to (100% + (125% +  15.625%) critical strike chance) AD against non-champions.

description2.value: Caitlyn may fire other empowered basic attacks until Headshot hits a target, which consumes all stacks.

description3.value: Enemies that step over a Yordle Snap Trap or are hit by 90 Caliber Net can grant an additional headshot at  1300 range for 1.8 seconds, without consuming stacks of Headshot.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * The bonus range from Rapid Firecannon will not have any effect during trap and net extended Headshot attacks. As with most on-hit physical damage, the bonus damage from Headshot will apply  life steal. Attacking wards or jungle plants will still generate stacks towards Headshot but the empowered attack will not be consumed. A stack is granted even if the attack is dodged The basic attack triggering Headshot can critically strike, but Headshot's damage remains unchanged if it does. Ability-granted Headshots are abilities that apply on-hit effects. They will not interact with effects that apply on-attack (including stacking Headshot). Energized, which normally stacks on-attack, has been special cased to stack on-hit for these empowered attacks. The bonus damage applies to turrets. Additional bolts from Runaan's Hurricane will not generate stacks towards Headshot but will benefit from the trap and net extended Headshot attack range.
notes.description: Displays additional information with effect table to the right.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Yordle Snap Trap.

blurb.value: Active: Caitlyn peroidically stocks a trap, up to a cap.

blurb2.value: Active: Caitlyn sets a trap at the target location. When sprung, the trap reveals and roots the enemy champion. The next headshot against a trapped target will deal bonus physical damage.

description.value: Passive: Caitlyn periodically stocks a Yordle Snap Trap charge, up to a maximum amount.

description2.value: Active: Caitlyn sets a visible untargetable trap at the target location which briefly grants sight of the area and arms after 1 second, lasting for a duration. After the maximum amount of traps is laid down, deploying another immediately destroys the oldest one.

description3.value: The next enemy champion that springs the trap is rooted for 1.5 seconds, revealed for 3 seconds, takes additional damage from Headshot, and becomes immune to Yordle Snap Traps for 3 seconds.

leveling3.value: Headshot Damage Increase:60 / 105 / 150 / 195 / 240 (+ 40 / 55 / 70 / 85 / 100% bonus AD)

description4.value: Yordle Snap Traps trigger simultaneously if stacked on top of each other, granting additional Headshots for each one beyond the first, but only increasing the damage for the first one.

notes.value:
* If Yordle Snap Traps are stacked on each other while the target is already rooted by one, the target is immune to them for:
 2 seconds for the 2nd and 3rd trap.
 3 seconds for the 4th and 5th trap.
 Completely immune to them after the 5th trap.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Ace in the Hole.

blurb.value: Active: Caitlyn targets an enemy champion and takes time to line up the perfect shot, dealing massive physical damage to them at a huge range. The target's allied champions can intercept the bullet for them.

description.value: Active: Caitlyn locks onto the target enemy champion and channels for 1 second, revealing them and revealing herself to enemies.

description2.value: Ace in the Hole is placed on a 5-second  cooldown if canceled.

description3.value: Once Caitlyn completes the channel, she fires a homing bullet toward the target that deals physical damage to the first enemy champion it hits.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * The following will cancel Ace in the Hole's channel (mana expenditure is not compensated): Caitlyn is interrupted. The target becomes untargetable. Caitlyn or her target dies. Caitlyn uses Flash. The ability also goes on a 5-second  cooldown if Caitlyn enters resurrection during the cast time. The cast time does not end prematurely but the channel will be immediately canceled the moment the cast time completes. If the target dies, becomes untargetable, or Caitlyn loses sight of them during the cast time, Ace in the Hole cancels but does not go on  cooldown nor consumes any mana. If the target dies after the bullet has been fired, the shot will continue towards their corpse and may still hit other enemy champions. If the target becomes untargetable after the bullet has been fired, the projectile will be destroyed. The target is revealed during the channel and while the bullet is in-flight.
